displayable_address: Carlton House, The Bishops Avenue N2
short_description: By order of the receivers Carlton House is a fine example of the imposing mansions located on the prestigious The Bishop’s Avenue– one of London’s most exclusive residential addresses. Situated in leafy Hampstead, the area is renowned for its historic parks and woodland but still offers excellent proximity to London’s financial district. The property is approached via a sweeping driveway allowing visitors the opportunity to fully appreciate the immense scale and quality of this impressive  mansion. The understated architecture of the frontage gives little indication of the luxury and opulence that lies within including 7 bedrooms all with lavish marble en-suite bathrooms, an underground pool complex, a self-contained staff apartment and even a 10-person Turkish bath. An impressive entrance hall with sweeping marble and wrought iron staircase welcomes visitors to Carlton House. A series of magnificent reception rooms lead off from the hall including a sitting room, a 50ft drawing room/ballroom, a family room, a private study and a dining room offering unlimited potential for grand entertaining. An electronic food lift connects the sophisticated catering kitchen in the lower ground floor with the smaller family kitchen above ensuring food always arrives hot and on time whether intended for an intimate gatheing or elegant social occasion. The main reception rooms have bespoke panelled ceilings with intricately designed crystal chandeliers, the walls are covered in tactile silk paper and the solid oak inlaid parquet floors exude a feeling of warmth. Windows are framed with triple-lined sculpted curtains with electronically controlled blinds. There is also a sophisticated electronically controlled system for climate and light settings, which allows temperature regulation and adjustable mood lighting. A centrally controlled stereo function pipes music into key rooms whithin the property. The cherry wood lined passenger lift escorts visitors to the upstairs floors and the collection of 7 bedrooms, all with en-suite marble bathrooms. A circular gallery is the focal point of the first floor, allowing an aerial view of the entrance hall below as well as providing access to 5 of the bedrooms. The stunning master bedroom suite includes a 'his n hers' walk in wardrobe, sitting room and a solid marble panelled bathroom with a centrally positioned round Jacuzzi bath. Plasma television screens are discreetly integrated in both the bathroom and within a custom-made consul in the bedroom. The master suite enjoys private access to a terrace overlooking the manicured gardens below as well as access to a further terrace which is shared with one other bedroom. The second floor is home to the two remaining bedrooms, both impressively large spaces and each with access to a private circular sitting room leading onto a front facing terrace. Few properties can boast a leisure complex as diverse and extravagant as Carlton House, featuring both a unique 'star lit' swimming pool as well as a luxurious solid marble and mosaic Turkish bath with capacity for ten people. There is also a fully-equipped gym, massage area and sauna. Other notable features include accomodation for two staff members and a substantial underground car park accesed via a car lift on the entrance forecourt. Carlton House occupies a world-renowned location on The Bishops Avenue - an idyllic semi-rural setting, but within easy reach of the centre of London. The nearby villages of Highgate and Hampstead boast a wide range of luxury boutiques, independent cafes and restaurants alongside some of the most desirable schools in London. Hampstead Heath offers an abundance of green space for leisure pursuits and panoramic views accross London. Further afield, The Bishops Avenue provides direct road links to London's West End, The City, the A1 and the North Circular (A406). London Overground and Underground stations are in walking distance and Heathrow, Luton and London City airports are easily accessible for private and commercial flights.

This breath taking and exquisite duplex penthouse apartment occupies the entire 6th and 7th floors of a much sought after apartment block in Clerkenwell, designed by"Form Design Architecture". Offering a combination of fluid open spaces and spectacular attention to detail it has been featured in various publications but more notably The Evening Standards Home and Property section Worlds best penthouses.The apartment is entered via a Picture gallery Hallway with faux suede panelled walls and recessed"Futronix"ceiling lighting with four windows offering views towards The City, Barbican and Shoreditch. A recessed pocket door then leads you into a most dramatic double height central gallery reception hall featuring a curved six meter high"Peruccheti"plastered wall and cantilevered staircase with oak treads. This opens onto the formal dining room and kitchen. The kitchen is bespoke with two distinct Nero Impala granite work areas including a 2 meter square island unit. The units and appliances are stainless steel with an integrated American style fridge freezer and a 144 bottle wine cooler. The formal dining room which also opens onto the double height hallway has a double aspect view towards St James Church on Clerkenwell Green and Central London. There are glazed doors leading onto a terrace and a concealed door leading to a storage room housing the entertainment system. The dining room has a silver leaf pillar and a pocket door with a"Robert O'Rea"silver leaf art installation. This leads into a versatile room which is currently used as a study but would also be a very comfortable third bedroom as it has built in wardrobes and its own en suite bathroom with"Grohe"fittings and"Bisazza"tiles. The inner hallway which is accessed from the study/third bedroom as well as the main entrance hall leads to a guest cloakroom and a utility room. The master bedroom suite is entered via double doors from the inner hallway and leads directly into the dressing room with wardrobes covered in a rich olive paper-backed silk providing ample hanging and storage space. The sleeping area which is dual aspect has glazed doors leading to its own private terrace with views of The City and St Paul's. Steps lead to the spacious en suite bathroom incorporating a free standing bath, American walnut table with twin ceramic basins and two way laundry cupboard. There are twin glazed doors one leading to a cloakroom and the other to a walk in Shower room with ceiling rain shower and limestone bench. The guest bedroom suite is also accessed from the inner hallway and has its own en suite shower room and built in cupboards with a back drop wall in faux silk. The sixth floor of the apartment has a consistent honed grey limestone flooring which creates an opulent flowing space. The reception room which occupies the entire 7th floor and is accessed via the double height central gallery reception hall and curved staircase has the most spectacular 360 degree elliptical view with uninterrupted view of The City and numerous important London Landmarks. A slot in the curved wall provides a framed view of St James Church on Clerkenwell Green while concertina by folding doors leading onto the most outstanding roof terrace. With an area of approximately 1350 square feet or 125 square meters the roof terrace arguably has the most impressive view of any Clerkenwell apartment with uninterrupted views of The City, St Paul's, The Shard as well as most recognisable London Landmarks. With both a timber decking and stone floor as well as a sun awning it offers a superb outside entertaining area. It has ample external lighting a water irrigation system and gas facility for a barbeque. Located on one of the best streets in Clerkenwell the apartment is located moments from Farringdon Underground and Mainline Stations which offers superb links to the City and West End and will, once completed offer excellent link to four of London's International Airports.

A truly unique development opportunity a stone's throw away from the amenities&transport links of Woolwich Arsenal. Rushgrove House is a rare opportunity to purchase a substantial London residence situated within its own walled grounds. Originally built in 1815 and extended in 1857, it was the residence of the Commandant of the Marine Barracks featuring extensive gardens and Mulgrave Pond, a historic lake formed in 1755 to provide water for the armoury and barracks, now a stocked lake. This Grade II listed property in the heart of Woolwich has over 8000 sq ft of accommodation on four floors and 3 acres of grounds including Mulgrave pond. There are 6 upper ground floor formal reception rooms, 11 rooms, 9bedroom's&offices plus a large fitted kitchen/breakfast room and several bathrooms over three floors, also has ample parking on a drive at the front of the property. The house has retained a wealth of period features but is now in need of sympathetic modernisation. The current owners have been granted planning permission to split the house into two separate dwellings but would prefer to sell to a single owner who will restore this historic house to its former grandeur.
